		<paragraph x="12" y="+4" width="605" height="0" style="headline" tabs="0" indent="0">&lt;B&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT LEADING=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;P ALIGN=&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;FONT FACE=&quot;Verdana&quot; SIZE=&quot;12&quot; COLOR=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;&lt;B&gt;Look carefully at the charts and complete the reports by choosing the preposition which best fits each gap. The preposition should be both grammatically correct and correct according to the information shown in the charts.&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</paragraph>
